y on the passages under examination, and to promote the study of modern performances – a practice which has so far been either restricted to Classical Reception or only theoretically acknowledged (if at all) by mainstream philological scholarship. This is a timely book on a topic of wide current interest across a range of interlocking disciplines: emotion studies, semiotics, narratology, information theory, and -most pertinently for this book- humour research.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aAristophanes. 4aHumor. 4aPoetik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAristophanes.  ahumour.  apoetics.  asurprise.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020 Englishz978311070483908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020z9783110704631oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831106771640 cprintz978311067698340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311067703440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110677034423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110677034/original  a978-3-11-065906-1  De Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCb2020  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  a978-3-11-069628-8  DG Ebook Package English 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 English